sentences.english: Lafuma added a rubber toe strip to protect you from rocks and roots.

sentences.english: Piscine mouth shoe, afterwards follow on current goes this year, if show, toe is like concealed, very sexy.

sentences.english: As it was dark, he stubbed his toe against the table leg.
sentences.chinese: 由于天暗看不见，他的脚趾碰到了桌子脚。

sentences.english: Wear your favorite pair of open-toe shoes or sandals.
sentences.chinese: 穿你喜欢的露脚趾的凉鞋或拖鞋。

sentences.english: I really admire your courage in biting your toe nail in public.
sentences.chinese: 我真信服你敢于在平易近众场所咬脚趾甲的勇气。

sentences.english: I walk around on my tippy toes.
sentences.chinese: 我走在我的周围毛尖脚趾。

sentences.english: The black stitching around the toe box gives the shoe a good punch.
sentences.chinese: 黑缝在脚趾箱子附近给鞋子好拳打。

sentences.english: Stretch your toes up and down several times.
sentences.chinese: 多次上下舒展你的脚趾。

sentences.english: Maintain knee and toe alignment to prevent knee torquing .
sentences.chinese: 维持膝和脚趾对准阻止膝转力矩。

sentences.english: The tops of the beggar's shoes had worn so thin that his toes were poking through.
sentences.chinese: 叫化子的鞋帮磨得很薄，脚趾头快要出来了。

sentences.english: Size 7 is too small. I can't even squeeze my toes into them.
sentences.chinese: 这双7号太小了，我连脚趾都塞不进去。

sentences.english: Place your right toe in line with your left heel.
sentences.chinese: 把右脚趾与左脚跟排在一直线上。

sentences.english: There should be a thumb’s width between the tip of your big toe and the top of the shoe.
sentences.chinese: 在你的大母脚趾尖与鞋头间应当有一拇指宽的空隙。

sentences.english: Thermal fleece lining with a spun-wool sock to keep your toes nice and cozy.
